## DESCRIPTION
## Michigan precalculus gateway problem: topic graph concepts
## ENDDESCRIPTION

DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

Context("Numeric");

$k = (qw( a b c d r s t u v w ))[random(0,9,1)];

$n = random(2,6,1);

$x = random(2,7,1);
$y = Compute(random(2,5,1));

$b = $x - $n*$y;

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

The point \(($x,$k)\) is on the graph of \(x = $b + $n y\). What is the
value of \($k\)?
$BR
\( $k = \) \{ $y->ans_rule(10) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS( $y->cmp() );

$s = ( $b > 0 ) ? '-' : '+';
$absb = abs($b);

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

We know that \(P = ($x, $k)\) lies on the line, so it must
satisfy the equation
\( $x = $b + $n $k \), so that
\( $k = \frac{$x $s $absb}{$n} = $y \).

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;

ENDDOCUMENT();
